        "title": "Data visualization with maps",
        "body": "<p>I'm building an app that will convert a conventional map to a data visualization where each district on the map is represented as a shape (circle, square?) and its size is dependent on the population of the district. Additionally, the shapes on the new map should have a somewhat accurate location relative to the other shapes. <\/p>\n\n<p>How would you approach this? <\/p>\n\n<p>EDIT: To be more specific, I have a spreadsheet with population counts for each district. In addition, I have a map (like google maps) that shows where each district is located geographically. I would like to output a visualization where each district is represented by a shape with its size dependent on the population. And, the shape's location on the visualization should convey where it lies relative to other districts geographically. <\/p>\n",
